First tennis lesson in the books!

Laney’s eyes were barely open as she came to find me after waking up this morning to ask if it was time to go to tennis. She did so great and can’t wait to play again next week! Looks like we may need to order some new gear to play with at home. 

I am so excited for the sports chapter to begin! I’ve always looked forward to the day I get to be the mom cheering from the sidelines! Though there’s still time before there’s actual matches or games for other sports she may want to try, I literally can’t wait! 

So here’s to trying new things and seeing what Laney enjoys to do most!

UA FLOW THE RUBERLESS!

Curry 8 ini sendiri merupakan sepatu pertama yang diluncurkan oleh Curry Brand, yang adalah brand terbaru milik Steph Curry dibawah naungan Under Armour. Ada teknologi baru juga yang diaplikasikan ke sepatu ini yaitu UA Flow, tapi apasih UA Flow itu?

Singkatnya, UA Flow merupakan teknologi cushioning milik Under Armour yang dimana bahan pembuatan midsole dan outsole nya tanpa menggunakan bahan karet sama sekali! Ya, brosist ga salah baca, its Rubberless! Berbeda dari kebanyakan sepatu basket yang outsolenya menggunakan karet di bagian outsolenya. 

Kelebihannya, sepatu ini jadi lebih grippy, lebih ringan, tidak muncul suara berdecit seperti sepatu dengan outsole karet pada umumnya, court-feel nya lebih terasa, dan memiliki abrasion resistance. Under Armour menemukan bahwa dengan membuang bagian karet pada outsolenya, sepatu akan menjadi lebih ringan sekitar 2 oz dari berat totalnya. 

Jadi makin penasaran kan sama sepatu yang satu ini? Brosist bisa langsung cek sepatu ini di website ncrsport.com atau bisa langsung KLIK LINK DI BIO!

After 3 trips to Lowe’s this morning to get supplies for the benches my husband and I are going to make for my herbs and succulents that we’ve been meaning to for the past couple years, I finally sat down and drew it out on graph paper Sunday and made a bill off materials (BOM).⁣
⁣
I’m always trying to maximize our dollar and know if I know how much I’m spending I can buy gift cards at Safeway and get points towards discounts on gas and groceries.  In my Lowe’s online cart Sunday they had the option to Ship to Home for free with what I was purchasing but by Monday when I had my gift card to purchase, it was no longer available.  Only Pickup from store or spend $79 to have a truck deliver it.⁣
⁣
My purchase was about $150 so I could not justify such an expensive delivery.  So 3 trips to 2 Lowe’s to get blocks, cut lumber and plastic sheets.  That apparent wiped me out that I needed a 2 hr sleep when I got home.⁣
⁣
Grateful we bought a heavy duty cart to haul heavy things 2-3 months ago from Harbor Freight because it came in handy hauling the blocks and lumber from the car to the backyard.  The Lowe’s guy in block area saw that I made 2 trips with my cart filled with heavy blocks decided to help me on my 3rd trip.⁣
⁣
And did you know a 2x12x16’ plank is really heavy? ⁣
⁣
⁣

.
「UNDER ARMOUR 
BRAND HOUSE 新宿」へ🚃
(以前"GUCCI"があった場所)
.
昨年 夏にネイビーの
マスクが販売される事を聞き
発売日に並び 1番大きい
サイズ(XL\2XL)を購入。
.
こちらのスポーツマスクは
口との距離が かなりあり
自分にとって嬉しい仕様👌
.
と言うのも一昨年、
副鼻腔炎の手術しましたが 
ずっと口呼吸が続いてたので
鼻呼吸が難しいのと💦
.
手術は全身麻酔で
気道を確保する際に声帯の
左右に肉芽(ポリープ)ができ
悪化し呼吸するのが苦しい為😭
.
その後 ネックウォーマー
タイプも登場した時も
発売日に伺い🚃
ブラックの大きいサイズ
(LG/XL)を購入。
.
ネックウォーマーとしての
機能もあり暖かく
マスクとして
呼吸もしやすいので
色違いも欲しいと
思ってた頃...
.
昨年末「GoToトラベル」で
2,000円分の地域共通
クーポン券も利用し
色違いのネイビーを買い
お手洗いで自撮りする😆
(笑顔でと思ったら目が...)
.
携わって頂いた
スタッフさん3人を
撮らせてもらいした📸
左上のモニターにアスリートが
ネックウォーマータイプの
マスク着用しランニングシーン🏃‍♀️
(写真 1枚目)
.
そして先日 春に向け
通常のマスクは1枚なので
色違いを購入しようと
新宿の病院帰りに寄り
.
前回 ネイビーでしたので
ブラックのマスクを購入🙆
.
今 キャンペーンで
購入したマスクに
その場で英数字を3文字まで
無料で圧着してもらえる
サービスが有りお願い😁
.
3階の奥スペースで
誕生日の数字「#13」を
アンダーアーマーマークの
反対側に付けてもらいました
嬉しいサービスですね✌️
.
またネックウォーマーの
タイプを何度か手洗いした時、
乾きづらいと相談😵
.
「鼻上のワイヤーを
傷めないように絞った後、
何度かブンブン振ってから
干して下さいと🙂」
アドバイス頂き実践☝️
.
以前よりも早く乾く
ようになりました👌
感謝です✨
.
スポーツマスクですが
普通のでは自分のように
呼吸がしづらい方にも
お勧めしたいです😙
.
ちなみにマスクの値段は
1枚 3,300円(税込)
手洗いで繰り返し
使えます🌿
.
いつも親切丁寧な対応、
ありがとうございました😊
.

∞
Barbell Hip Thrusts - 855x4 - Lifetime PR

Always working hard for those glute gains!! 🍑🍑🍑 Leg and glute days just aren't complete without a good hip thrusting session! 💪🍑🦵

I was feeling especially inspired on this day, so I decided to see what I could accomplish. I slowly built up to my final set of 855 lbs for 4 reps, with a pause at full contraction on top of each rep. The 4th rep was a grind, but I did my best and held it at the top for as long as I could. My glutes are definitely going to feel it tomorrow 🥲 Also, if anyone knows of a good olympic bar that can hold more than 9 plates per side please let me know.

I feel that a lot of people don't realize that biggest and most important part of lifting, or strength training or anything in life really, is the power of your mind, and all that you're willing to go through to accomplish something that's important and meaningful to you. I have always believed that if your mind, body, heart and soul are at one, you can accomplish absolutely anything in this world. Thank you @jamie.leigh.norman for coaching me, lifting with me and inspiring me on this day ✨

AND the leggings: My mind that used to wander to my waistband that was rolling, sagging, drooping, etc does not anymore thanks to these leggings. The no-slip waistband design ensures that both my mental and physical energy is better spent where it belongs: on my workout & moving seamlessly throughout my day. 🏃🏻‍♀️The side drop-in pocket is clutch for a phone &/or keys. Running 5km every day for a year in aid of Team Hill Charitable Trust & Destination Florida Children’s Charity

Wow! Almost there... If you haven’t seen my previous post, I will be celebrating my final challenge day [365 days of running] on March 31st by running a marathon distance, stopping by both Charity HQ’s, visiting some of my favourite places, and running with a few supporters along the way, ending up at @mediacityuk in Salford, Manchester... 😅

If 5k every day for a year wasn’t enough, thought I’d up a notch for the final day, I mean, why not?! 😁👌🏻

🗺 Today’s Strava GPS swindled me out of a km this morning- then when I’d made it up, it decided to give it back to me! Ran loops around my estate for the final 1km (that I didn’t have to do) which was fun!! All in preparation for day 365, of course...

🙏🏻 Thank you so much for all the support, my fundraising is still ticking away, and now- more than ever, if you can donate any amount possible, please visit the link in my bio! Mission £5k for 5k every day is now ON! 💪🏻

IMPACT. It’s a way of life. It’s a mindset. It’s a mantra I live by DAILY. Especially right now through all that’s going on.

I want to share my acronym for I.M.P.A.C.T. with you today because I think it’s important we understand the WHY behind we do what we do…⠀
⠀
What does IMPACT stand for?⠀
I = Live INSPIRED. Stay motivated and “in-spirit”. ⠀
M = MASTER ur craft. Maniacally focus on best habits right now so u can dial up ur inspiration.⠀
P = Play at World Class. That’s the MINDSET of a champion. That’s the #GetUrMindRight part.⠀
A = Take ACTION. What do u want? Go get it.
C = Condition for greatness! Whether it’s your body, mind, or spirit, it takes dedication and commitment to your conditioning to amp it up and improve your health and well-being.
T = Be TENACIOUS. The fervor, spirit, and ENERGY needed to show up everyday to en ur best.⠀
⠀
You can always go back to episodes 1 & 2 of the #ToddDurkinIMPACTShow podcast and listen deeply to what it means also!⠀
⠀
Today, live IMPACT in all you do. And if ur feeling super motivated, drop down and flex into an IMPACT pose. That’s guaranteed to #GetUrMindRight!⠀
⠀
Much love...and much IMPACT!!⠀

DISCIPLINE WORKS ALWAYS. Every single time!!⠀
⠀
☄️If there is one KEY element to success in anything and especially the gym/fitness/health it is DISCIPLINE. If you have the self discipline to put in the hard work & sacrifice every day you will reap the rewards. This ultimately will lead to greater prosperity in the long run. ⠀
⠀
☄️Yes there are many distractions and I myself can give into them but I’ve learned over time how to get back on the path due to having a strong self discipline. Don’t beat yourself up for having that takeaway or not going the gym on a certain day, just see each day as a new day to recharge and go again to reach your goals. ⠀
⠀
☄️I gained my discipline fitness wise from my first ever PT teaching me that before bed and after waking up I should do ‘x’ press ups, ‘x’ sit ups, ‘x’squats and hold a plank for ‘x’ amount of time. While very simple this routine built in the DISCIPLINE I needed to progress. It bloody worked.

-Greater chance of success 
-Better Relationships
-Better Financial Health
-Fewer Regrets
-Improved Time Management 
-See things through to the end

⠀

Myth: weight loss is about calories in and calories out.

If only it were this easy. Weight loss is about everything. Sleep. Stress. Hormones. Genetics. Quality of food. Consistency. Water intake. All the things. 
It is easier for some, and harder for others.

I try to tell my clients focus on gaining strength, and stability. Then track your muscle mass, and body fat as better gauges of your fitness and health then your weight alone. Weight is a measurement tool that can help a lot with long-term health risks, and preventative care. It should just never be used alone.

Focus on strength gains, muscle mass, bf, and circumference with your weight goals 💪🏻. This may help put your mind at ease while trying to accomplish a number range on the scale.

caption:
Run 1️⃣ of week 6️⃣ 

6 weeks into recovery and I’m feeling bloody good! No more pain and just generally in a great mood of late 🏃🏻‍♂️ 

A huge thank you to @allsportstherapy for the help and guidance you’ve given me to be able to get back to being a pain free runner 🤩 

I was honestly so lost and confused before I went to see Fiona, she diagnosed the issue straight away and we worked on it from there. I was given exercises to do at home each time I saw her and I’m on late stage rehab now. Slowly my confidence has built up and I’ve been running pain free for over a week now 🥳 long may it continue! If anyone has any injury concerns I fully recommend @allsportstherapy who have always looked after me, even when I used to be an overweight average footballer 🤣

Obviously I will be sticking to my exercises and I will continue to build my distance up over the coming weeks before my next training block begins 🏃🏻‍♂️

caption:
This warm weather the past week has been pretty awesome! 

Definitely has me excited for spring and summer. 

But honestly, I wouldn’t appreciate the warmer months as much if it wasn’t for winter. 

I have a respect for winter because it’s cold, it’s dark, it’s just plain hard. 

Going through the hard times makes you really appreciate the good times. 

This can relate in all aspects of life. 

Learning to accept the hard things and just keep moving one day at a time knowing you’re one step closer to a better destination is so important. 

For me, I truly love the process of being better than I was yesterday. 

If it wasn’t for the hard work, consistency, sacrifices and just hard shit, 

How could one truly appreciate how far they’ve come? 

Just a reminder to enjoy the hard days (winter) because the good days are soon to follow.

caption:
Привет спортсмены 🤚
.
Сегодня мы поговорим о особенностях жима штанги лёжа для новичков.💪
Упражнение жима штанги лежа не является простым и легким. У него есть свои нюансы, не зная которых начинающие спортсмены делают грубые ошибки при его выполнении, что зачастую ведет к снижению эффективности тренировок. Остановимся на особенностях этого упражнения подробнее.
.
Жим лежа является базовым многосуставным упражнением. Данное упражнение является оптимальным для развития силы и повышения массы всех мышечных групп верней части тела. Так, во время выполнения данного упражнения основную нагрузку получает большая грудная мышца. Также задействуют трицепсы и дельтоиды.
.
Ни один наминающий атлет, выполняющий упражнения жима штанги, не смог избежать разного рода ошибок, так или иначе снижающих эффективность занятий. На собственном опыте давайте рассмотрим самые распространенные из них:
🔻Пренебрежение разминкой - Качественная разминка является залогом успеха всей тренировки. Так, чтобы избежать травм и неприятных ощущений необходимо в обязательном порядке перед началом многосуставных упражнений как следует "разогреться".
🔻Использование позы "мостик" - Многие начинающие атлеты во время занятий применяют позу "мостик" (приподнимая таз и выгибая поясницу во время жима). Данная поза значительно упрощает жим. Но в случае, если у спортсмена мышцы ослаблены, то он гарантировано получит травму во время жима.
🔻Жим в одиночестве - Не каждый атлет на тренировках имеет страхующего партнера. Однако, его присутствие крайне необходимо уже при работе со средним весом снаряда 
.
И это не все ошибки, которые  я хотел вам рассказать.
.
Всем спорта и хорошей недели ☺️💪🔥
.

POST WORKOUT SELFIE 🤳🏼

Took about 5 months off the gym & working out, and haven’t done yoga for a month... now kicking myself for not putting up with the home workouts 🥲

Honestly I was tired from uni, lacking that motivation, and seeing other amazing fitness instagram-ers doing so well.. it made me even less motivated! 🦥

But i’m going to get that baseline strength back and do my hypertrophy training before the gyms open again 💪🏼

Am I feeling motivated again yet? Honestly no, but I know I can get there again and now I have fitness goals again 🎯🌟

10km, barrière psychologique?
C’est fou comme cette distance ne laisse personne indiffèrent.
Ca rappele forcément les débuts en course où l’objectif ultime est d’arriver à 10km sur son appli Nike, scotché sur le bras.
Un jour, tu craques au 8ieme km agonisant, la bouche sèche, la grosse transpiration, tu as mal partout et tu as la MEGA BONNE IDÉE DE te dire:
« Fuck, je vais les faire mais je ne suis pas sûr de pouvoir en sortir vivant » 
Et tu les finis en tournant autour de chez toi pour faire 10km PIL POIL !!!
Avec du recul, c’est quand même un super souvenir cette insouciance, loin de penser aux blessures ou autres.

Aujourd’hui, l’objectif est tout autre, le but est de faire 10km et surtout de le refaire sur le long terme, sans griller les étapes.
Alors à toi qui débute ou qui revient de blessure ou qui n’est pas serein à l’idée de faire 10km, je n’aurai qu’un seul conseil, fais les quand tu sentiras que ton corp est prêt à produire et à reproduire cet effort.
Tu peux le faire une fois pour te prouver à toi même que tu es capable (mon cas today) mais n’oublie pas de faire des séances plus courte, ce n’est pas une régression, c’est juste que tu as dit à ton corps:
« Hey, les muscles et les tendons, je suis capable de faire 10km donc adaptez vous à ca » 
et ton corps te répondra :
« ok on a vu, on en a chier donc laisse nous le temps de régénérer avec 2/3 jours off ou plus et de nous adapter en faisant des séances plus courtes »
L’objectif est de le faire, et de pouvoir le refaire ✌🏼
.
Qui s’est reconnu dans ma description du 1er 10KM ?!? 
(Je me suis décrit hein 😂😂)
.
.
.

⠀
🔸Ещё не так давно кроссовки расценивались как обувь, уместная только во время спорта, а на сочетание сникеров, например, с платьем смотрели так же неодобрительно, как на микс белого и жёлтого золота.

First run out in the Pegasus 36.

Today was a steady run to test out my new Pegasus 36’s. I didn’t want to be pushing it too hard after yesterday’s run.

First thoughts of the the shoes are good, they feel light on the feet, the mesh upper is breathable, the shoe fits brilliantly around the heel and keeps your feet locked in place once tied.

The shoe feels responsive when changing pace during the run, and seems to be best suited for the quicker paces. 

Obviously I will have to take them out a few more times before I know exactly how I feel on them, but for now they seem like a great addition to the collection.

3 совета по спортивному питанию для спортсменов👇🏼

Питание - топливо для организма. Мы приготовили 3 совета по питанию во время активных занятий спортом:

1️⃣Для борьбы с окислением и разрушением клеток во время анаэробных тренировок вам необходимо принимать антиоксиданты. Они есть в составе SIS GO ISOTONIC ENERGY GELS  с кофеином и вкусом фруктового салата.

2️⃣Для интенсивных тренировок в качестве источника энергии спортсменам необходимы богатые питательными веществами углеводы. SIS GO ENERGY BAKE содержит 30 г углеводов, необходимых для поддержания уровня
энергии во время длительных физических нагрузок. 
А SIS GO ISOTONIC ENERGY GELS буквально сразу обеспечивает организм необходимой энергией благодаря специальной усваиваемой формуле.

3️⃣Во время тренировки с потом организм теряет и питательные вещества.Восполнить потери и значительно повысить выносливость вам поможет SIS GO HYDRO TABLET  содержит точный уровень натрия и других электролитов, необходимых для поддержания водно-солевого баланса в клетках и обеспечивающий организм витаминами и минералами, потерянные через потоотделение.

Используйте продукцию SIS во время активных занятий спортом и вы легко добьётесь поставленых целей и новых рекордов🏃🏼‍♀️

Переходите по ссылке в шапке профиля и восполняйте энергию с брендом SIS⬆️

Every Tuesday at 7:30pm I lead a gentle yoga class at @karibfit in Silver Spring, MD. 

Last week I had a student athlete (track) attend class because according to him his muscles needed to be stretched. After class he and his mom inquired about private 1:1 😊

The benefits of stretching our muscles include: increasing range of motion, preventing injury, and decrease muscle soreness.

Gentle Flow Yoga is geared specifically for those new to yoga or those who are interested in a gentle practice. This class incorporates simple flowing sequences to warm up the body, as well as slower paced movements focusing on alignment, strength, balance, and flexibility. No experience or flexibility required. Participants are encouraged to bring their own props (such as blankets and pillows).

Class space is limited. Link to book is in my bio.

Movement is healing!

🍂¿Eres una hoja cayendo?🍃
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
🤨Observo últimamente que la gente anda pendiente de los/as compañeros/as... y hay dos tipos de personas🧐

 ¿Cuál eres?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
👉🏼1- Las personas que cuando el resto hacen poco se ponen al mismo nivel, diciendo eso de: si él/ella no hace yo tampoco. No voy a hacer su trabajo o, si lo hago no me lo van a reconocer... y demás mensajes🧐

Suelo decir a quien me rodea que es la metáfora de “la hoja cayendo”🍂🍃🍂🍃
Va oscilando de lado a lado, pero siempre tiene una trayectoria descendente. Que mi compi hace poco, pues yo menos. Y a la larga eso no lleva a ningún sitio... si eres de los que están así, para y reflexiona. ¿Es tu culpa o es del entorno? Si eres jefe/a y lo detectas quizás necesitas incentivar o modificar para que esa dinámica se corte...😶

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
👉🏼2-Las personas que se centran en ellos, su independencia y profesionalidad, e intentan mejorar, progresar y crecer. A veces se frustran con el entorno y con ellos mismos por ser tan perfeccionistas. Se equivocan pero aprenden, mira la competencia desde otra perspectiva... y no se dan por vencidos/as si no se les reconoce🌷🌸 

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
✍🏼El problema muchas veces es que los de arriba deberían meter más caña a los que lo hacen mal, en vez de cargar de trabajo a los que lo hacen bien... ¿incompetencia?🤷🏻‍♂️
Muy de España eso...

¿Te molesta algo? 🤜🏼Cámbialo🤛🏼 

📖Un consejo:

“Haz los cambios cuando estés bien; si no, admitirás cualquier propuesta”

今日の練習風景﻿
﻿
◎1年　黒島選手コメント﻿
今日は、紅白をしてフィジカルトレーニングをしました。﻿
紅白では、自分はボールを受けた時に、前に行こうとせずに中や後ろにパスを出すことが多くて、前線の選手の足元や裏のスペースへのパスを狙えなかったので、改善していきたいです。﻿
チームとしては、全体的に、ラインを上げるのが遅れていたのでしっかり声かけをして組織力を高めていきたいです。﻿
﻿
﻿
◎2年  屋冨祖選手コメント﻿
今日の練習は久しぶりに紅白戦をしました。自分は怪我あけだったのでBチームのところででました。Aチームで出ていた時とは違い上手くいかないところが多々あったけど、近くにいる選手達と話しながら段々とビルドアップで前に進むことができ、シュートの本数も増えてたので良かったです。でもまだまだビルドアップでのミスが目立つのでそこを修正していきたいです。﻿
試合をしてAチームもBチームもあまり差はないと感じ、新1年生も入ってきたらさらにスタメン争いが激しくなるので、一人一人が試合に出たいという気持ちをもって今後の練習に励んでいけばチームも強くなると思うので、これから頑張っていきたいです。﻿

6:05am - eat third meal, get ready for work. 
8:00am- work

My schedule varies depending on what I have going on for that day.

🔥JBL& Under Armour聯名款 True Wireless Flash X 真無線運動耳機🔥
True Wireless Flash X 為防水耳機
防水係數 IPX7，可落入一公尺內的水中30分鐘
在做大量爆汗的運動也不用擔心汗水影響耳機的品質~

☀️UA耳機外觀不錯，具設計感

☀️側面有防止手滑的防滑塊 (非常貼心的功能)

☀️讓艾莉兒大大心動的是它有一個鯊魚鰭的設計，可緊緊貼在耳廓上
不管是在慢跑及踩飛輪，大幅度的擺動，有鯊魚鰭完全不用怕耳機會掉落的困擾

☀️音質偏向清新
不會有厚重的重低音
音質清脆在運動時也較愉快

☀️UA多功能耳機，按鍵簡單操作方便(就左右各一個鍵而已)
==左耳==
True Wireless Flash X 戴上後可緊密貼在耳裡，未設定情況是聽不太到人聲
不過他們有特別技術，只要按壓左耳一下，
會降低一些音樂(80%)並放大語音(20%)，再按一下恢復95%全音樂功能
若覺得還是聽不太清楚可連續按壓兩下
音樂與外界人聲會是各一半的比例（50%）
這樣貼心設計讓懶人艾莉兒，不用拿下耳機也可以輕鬆與大家溝通

==右耳==
按一下  接電話/暫停
按兩下  下一首歌曲

☀️此真無限運動耳機續航力可達到 50小時
僅通勤時間使用的話，可將近一個月不充電都沒有問題

Saamalla aikaan paniikin saavat tietyt tahot aikaa ja liiketilaa omalla kohdallaan näkymättömissä. Joo ja mä pidän tota maskia tasan kahdesta syystä se on musta ja jengi ei nää kuka ritsaa kaupasta.  No eikai kakkonen oli valehdeltu optio. Oikea vastaus on että ei saisi pahan suovia katseita tähän suuntaan. Yhtään enempää kun niitä pystyy saamaan. 

Eräs viisivuotias neito totesi ei toi rätti suojaa oikeesti mitää kun se likaisena laitetaan taskuun ja takasi. (Jos sen tajuaa lapsiki niin....) Se on mihin opettaa ja mitä tietää.  Tärkeä tieto oli se kuka ajoi veneen espanjaan joskus eikä se että venezuelas oli totaali inflaatio ja Amazon palaa vieläkin.  Sisään rakennettu järjestelmä

Onnittelen päätöntä päätäntää siitä miten saatte pienet yhtiöt nurin ja isommatkin. Jos ei kuulu johtokunta 1vereen niin nurin vaan keinolla millä tahansa. Ihmiset paniikkiin. No ne on ollut panikiis jo syntymästä suurin osa. 
Oikein loistavaa päivää maskit naamalle ja menoksi. Peskää kätenne. Joku pesee ne tyyliikkäämmin. Peittämää silmämme ja odottakaa paras osuus on tulossa

“How are you so motivated to get up in the mornings?!”

Although I feel like I talk about this quite a lot on here, it is still the most asked question I receive. So here’s why and how I do it!

• the feeling of “cba” is only temporary.
• that endorphin rush is divineee.
• the rest of my day is more positive, productive, mood & self-confidence boosted.
• @beltr.uk oats taste even better! 

I very veryyy rarely spring out of bed and want to get sweaty. But knowing the WHY is what makes me get up and do it. Why wouldn’t you want to set yourself up for a positive productive day ahead?! 

And can I just reiterate... you don’t have to do a crazy ass session to achieve this goal. Getting your body moving in whatever way suits you eg yoga, walking, pilates will undoubtably benefit you in more ways than one! 😅

If you’re someone who is needing that extra kick up the backside.. this is me telling you.. just do it! Tomorrow morning, set your alarm clock an hour or 30 minutes before you usually get up. Fight that initial “cba”. And get that body moving and mind boosted! You will feel amazing for it. I promise you. 🙏🏼

#StartStrongStayStrong 

(Ps the Lumie light was a fabulous investment for those who want a relaxing getting up. What a dream)

Теперь я в этом окончательно убедился 😃 шучу, клевая майка! Как по мне, так все эти карантины-шмарантины только усиливают мотивацию заниматься собой с удвоенной силой. И насчёт питания немножко вставлю. Можете сколько угодно шутить, что я дрыщ и тд, но всего 2 месяца вкусного, полезного потребления калорий из правильных продуктов под чутким руководством @sough_  и я заметно изменился внешне. Не говоря уже про самочувствие и общую работу всех систем организма. Парни, очень рекомендую, от ПП либидо скакануло как в 18 лет 😈💪😃 Ну что, носы не вешаем, становимся лучше, скоро лето! Всем спорт! ❤️ #personaltrainer #projectrock #fitness #anticovid #soughismybabygirl

✅Joel Embiid & Embiid One

➡️A season without precedent has laid the foundation for Joel Embiid’s debut signature performance footwear with Under Armour. Like Joel and his style of play, the UA Embiid One is a sneaker without limits or a designated position. And, as a positionless shoe, it’s designed to elevate any player’s on-court performance - from the 5 to the 1.

➡️Known as The Process (or “Do-a-180” for you “Jeopardy” fans), Joel continues to be a force in the league and the literal centerpiece of the 76ers’ recent success. Since stepping on the court, Embiid has averaged 24.1 points and 11.5 rebounds to go along with 1.8 blocks and 3.1 assists. Standing tall at 7’, his size, strength, and reach make him a threat under either basket, while his quickness and ball-handling abilities enable him to help spread and push the floor. 

➡️Philadelphia has surged into the playoffs the last three seasons, and remains eager to progress beyond the conference semis. Joel is hungry to add to his legacy and help deliver on a promise he made early on in his career. You know the one. 

➡️The design team considered every detail of the UA Embiid One, from the materials to the potential weight distribution to the traction with Joel’s size and versatility in mind. It truly is a position-less shoe.

🇩🇪 Bringt frischen Wind in dein Lauftraining: Der neue Under Armour Flow Velociti Wind. 🌬️⁠
⁠
Die neue, durchgehende FLOW-Zwischensohle bietet dir eine reaktionsschnelle Dämpfung. Durch die Verarbeitung eines einzigen Materialstückes ist das Material weniger verschleißanfällig. Und dank dieser langlebigen Eigenschaften hat sich Under Armour dazu entschieden, keine zusätzliche Gummilaufsohle in diesen Schuh zu integrieren. Das grobe Profil der Zwischensohle fungiert damit als Laufsohle und bietet guten Grip und Traktion.🏃🏻‍♀️⁠
⁠⁠
Mit diesem neutralen Laufschuh an den Füßen kann dich nichts und niemand aufhalten. Der Schuh eignet sich perfekt für mittellange Distanzen und gibt dir das Gefühl von Rückenwind. Zudem ist der Schuh mit der MapMyRun-App kompatibel – für ein ultimatives Lauf-Coaching. ⁠🔥⁠
⁠
🇬🇧⁠ Bring a breath of fresh air to your running training with the new Under Armour Flow Velociti Wind. 🌬️⁠
⁠
The new, full-length FLOW midsole provides responsive cushioning. By using a single piece of material, the sole is less prone to wear. Because of this, Under Armour decided to not integrate an additional rubber outsole on the shoe. Instead the coarse profile of the midsole also functions as an outsole and offers good grip and traction. 🏃🏻‍♀️⁠
⁠⁠
With this neutral running shoe on your feet, nothing and nobody can stop you. The shoe is perfect for middle-long distances and let’s you feel like you’ve go the wind in your back. The shoe is also compatible with the MapMyRun app - for the ultimate running coach experience.⁠ 🌬️⁠
⁠

身体は素直🌿
．
実は最近トレーニングなまけてました😞
．
パソコンでの作業も多く、座りっぱなし🙅‍♀️
レッスンをしている時は自分は身体を動かさないので
疲れていると、よし！動くぞ！っていう気になれずで
肩こりあるし背中も痛いし
身体にメリハリがなくなってきたかも、、
と思っていました🥲🥲🥲
．
そうすると気分もパッとしないし
身体のメリハリだけではなくて
生活のメリハリとなくなってることに気づいたのです！
．
これじゃだめだなとまずはじめたのが
【ストレッチ】
これ本当に大切さを実感しました。
身体ガチガチなことにストレッチして初めて気付きました。
身体を知るきっかけにもなるし
伸びて重たい身体がスッキリしました！

すごく簡易的なものです！
・脚を伸ばして脚のストレッチ
・身体を横に倒して体側のストレッチ
・身体を前に倒して背中のストレッチ
キープは短くても30秒以上は必ず！
長くできれば90秒ほど呼吸しながらキープ
できるとよいですね❣️
ストレッチは基本難しいことは考えず
伸びてる感覚があればいいです！
※痛いまでいくと筋肉びっくりして
縮む原因にもなるのできた気持ちいくらい
．
あとは、【ピラティスマシン使ってトレーニング】
とりあえず身体をマシンに預けてみました
そしたら数回で身体の変化が目に見てわかってきたんです〜🥺
．
．
《改めて思ったこと》
🌻自分の身体と向き合うことが大切
🌻そして身体の状況を知ることが大切
🌻身体は正直
🌻身体を動かすと気分もスッキリ
🌻身体が変わると心がスッキリ
．
．
ぜひ一緒に身体を動かす習慣をつけましょう！
そしてストレッチしたり鏡をみたり、自分の変化に気づいてあげるための習慣を😌🌱
．
．

ホールド感あってすっごく着やすい！！

제스트 시설도 깨끗하고 기물들도 잘 관리되어 있고 코치님들도 유능하다고 생각합니다
운동하면서 PT 사기도 당해보고😇
인성 문제 있는 코치님들도 만나봤기 때문에🙄
예를 들면 본인 욕심에 무리한 무게를 강요해서 부상을 유발하게 만든다던가
회원을 을이라고 생각하면서 가르쳐 주는게 아니라 혼낸다던가
식단을 짜준다고 해놓고 모른척하거나
엉뚱한 자격증을 소지하고 있다던가
다친 회원을 방치한다던가
공사 구분을 못해서 구설수에 오른다던가
왜?라는 질문에 시원하게 답변을 못해주거나
무리를 지어서 기싸움을 한다던가
이렇게 적어 놓고 보니 참 다양하네요🥲
아무튼 이곳에선 저런 일들을 경험하지 못했습니다
오히려 기존 회원분들이 신규 회원을 챙겨주려는 느낌이 들어서
덕분에 편안한 분위기에서 운동 가능했어요
스트레스 풀러 갔는데 도리어 스트레스 받으면 진짜 딥빡인거 다들 아시죠?😂🤣
크로스핏을 어렵게 생각하시는 분들이 많은데
정해진 오늘의 운동에서 개개인마다 난이도를 조절해서 진행하기 때문에
전혀 두려워하실 필요가 없답니다☺️
마음 같아선 쭉 제스트에서 운동하고 싶지만 개인 사정으로 불가능해져서 아쉬운 마음에 적어보는 내돈내산 후기입니다🥰
저는 이용준 코치님이랑 신나래 코치님 수업 추천👍🏽👍🏽

Hit it hard today. Bodyweight workout for the win.
I am trying to get back to where I was pre move. 
Open and honest moment. I have struggled on and off the last bit of time. Multiple things going on and I let my emotions and heart lead me strongly which is great but can also be draining and be a source of drastic hurt. 
Fitness has been a source of relaxation and stress relief for majority of my life. 
Physical health is important for mental health so.....much. 
I have also learned through trials and obstacles. 
To quote Spiderman "I always get back up"
I have amazing family, friends, and faith, most importantly a beautiful daughter that keeps me striving to reach for my stars and i will reach them.
Also, side note very happy to get that vascular going on. Love it. Hahaha.

“I have a tendency to exceed expectancies, trying to build a legacy with low sleep dependency, trying to leap to where the legends sleep and etch my name on the tenancy”

Yep, it’s the serial midnight oil burner doing what he does best 🔥🕯

Life is made up of choices. Every choice has a degree of sacrifice or risk. Ironically, you have to choose which choices are worth that potential sacrfice and risk.

There are limited hours in each day. And it is tough to be a great father, son, husband, mentor, student, friend and colleague within those hours. However I’m not willing to sacrifice being great at those things, that’s my choice.

So my sacrifice is sleep... and I’m ok with that. The risk is that I look way too old before my time. But I have made 2 other choices to counteract that.. 1 is #collagenskinbooster from #herbalifenutrition . Just started my collagen journey so let’s see how that goes! 

And 2 is to meditate daily whilst repeatedly chanting one of the most divine and unshakeable, universal truths known to us all... “black don’t crack” 🤣🤣💪🏽 helps me to sleep easier when I do actually get around to sleeping!

Greatness does not sleep, so every moment I am not chasing it, it is getting further away...

🔥WE ARE DEFINED BY THE LIMITATIONS WE IMPOSE ON YOURSELVES .

Because every push makes the next challenge a lot easier to accomplish. We are reshaping the future by pushing through  our daily struggles . If you have an idea💡 , do something about it. 1) Ontem no All-Star Game de 2021 em Atlanta, aconteceu algo inimaginável:

LeBron James e Stephen Curry jogaram juntos, no mesmo time, pela primeira vez na história. 

2) Os rivais de uma geração:

Disputaram 4 Finais um contra o outro. 

Curry levando a melhor, vencendo em 3 ocasiões. 

Curioso é que ele não levou nenhum prêmio de MVP das Finais, como você pode perceber no Consagrômetro. 

O LeBron apesar de ter perdido 3 vezes ganhou a Final mais difícil da história e levou os CAVS a se tornar o primeiro time a virar uma série de final estando perdendo ela por 3-1. 

4) O discurso dicotômico que separa os dois jogadores: sobre LeBron James ser mais compenetrado e focado, enquanto Curry é apenas um garoto brincando na quadra. É uma besteira. 

Digo isso pela compatibilidade no caminho de ambos em busca da grandeza:

Curry como o melhor arremessador de todos os tempos e um dos melhores jogadores da história. 

LeBron como o jogador mais completo de todos os tempos e um dos melhores (talvez, o melhor) jogador da história. 

5) Além dessa concordância nos objetivos, temos um fato curioso:

Os dois nasceram no mesmo hospital, em Akron - Ohio. 

A mística está presente. 

Eu prefiro a mágica. 

6) Certamente, farei de tudo para meu filho nascer por lá também. 

7) Pra ver algumas fotos e vídeos do Final de Semanas das estrelas é só ir lá no nosso STORIES 📲

8) O CONSAGRÔMETRO é toda segunda-feira 12:30. Hoje atrasou.

Took me a while to come to terms about sharing these pictures, so here we are!!! A little thread ✨✨

Feeling shy, a bit anxious, worried (about what people may think of me showing parts of me I haven’t shown before) feeling like I’m reconstructing myself and it makes me also feel empowered, confident, and capable of more.

Growing up in a social construct of “you have to be a certain way to be considered pretty” damages the way how you see yourself as a teenager and as a young adult. It truly tarnishes how you see yourself and how you want other to see you. In my 30’s now and I haven’t felt this comfortable in my own body for a very very long time.

Women have been subjected to follow a certain societal construct that was made up by controlling and backwards mindsets. If a woman doesn’t follow such “rules” then people consider them a slut🙅🏻‍♀️, a weirdo, wrong🙅🏻‍♀️, ugly, and dumb... among many more names... and this is SO wrong!! So so sooooo wrong. Everyday is a new day to STOP this backward mindset that makes people think that way! To stand up together as women and say “No, I’m breaking those chains!” I’m living my life guilt free of my body, my thoughts and retaking my autonomy.

We are fierce, we are caring, and nurturing, we are more than capable to achieve our goals and resilient to keep on fighting for them. ✨💖Happy International Women’s day you badass Queens out there!!💖✨
.
.
.
And thank you to all of the amazing men who not only support the women in their lives but believe in them and hype them up! You are amazing! Thank you for standing up for and with us! I am very lucky and blessed to have an amazing guy by my side supporting my endeavors and decisions. ILY @bigbirdoffie ♥️

El día amenazaba lluvia y se acaba de levantar viento. Perfecto para poner a prueba la chaqueta Impasse Flight de @underarmour. Es súper ligera y lleva aperturas en las sisas para mejorar la ventilación. 

Como cortavientos, un 10. Las gotas de lluvia que me han caído - no muchas- las ha parado bien (véase la segunda foto, iba pa’ lo negro). En transpirabilidad quizás esperaba un pelín más en la parte superior de la espalda. Con el sol he acumulado algo de sudor. 

Una de las cosas que más me gustan es que se puede plegar dentro de la manga con una banda elástica para colgar del antebrazo o la muñeca si finalmente no llueve. No ha sido el caso, pero de haber seguido el sol como en los primeros kilómetros me lo hubiera acabado quitando. 

En fin, una prenda ligera con la que contar para la primavera loca de Madrid. 

Por cierto, lo rojo de debajo es el cinturón portageles (y porta móvil) de @lurbelpg . Las mallas son de hace varias temporadas de @reebok y me siguen rechiflando. Y la camiseta de tirantes, regalo de Navidad 2019 de @reto21k . Miss U girl 😘

2019 Take me #BACK 😫 lol

Don’t mind the theatrics I know as well as anyBODY change is imminent; World crisis or no. That said, when these changes occur it’s natural to find yourself looking back….Pun intended.

Due to many life changes I find myself in a fitness catharsis where I have now become my own fit goal. On one hand that does mean I have lost the oh so coveted “gainz” since this picture was taken but on the other hand it also means I now have a goal that is SO attainable I have actually accomplished it once before. We don’t always set such realistic fit goals so to have such a intimate relationship to the mark is a bit comforting.

Now this picture, this version of me, is by no means the end game. We all know it never really ends when you love it. But for now I’ll hold myself up as the metric by which I shall measure my success. We’re only ever in competition with ourselves anyway. 💪🏾

Trust the process!! Here are a few pics of me rolling for the very first time in 2019. I weighed 187 lbs. could barely do a push-up, hid the fact that I was very unhappy behind a smile and a joke. Now look at the girl in pink... she used the lessons, motivation, encouragement, and support to face her fears! That woman in pink is facing worries and challenges EVERY DAMN DAY with determination to carve her own path and be in charge of her own happiness. My security in terms of lifestyle and possessions is MUCH less solid now, some days feel like if I can just avoid sliding backwards in this thing called life than it’s enough. I take baby steps, and somehow God makes each step count toward my growth and progress. I am happy, and pushing forward. Transformation is HARD and SCARY, but Oh SO worth it!! I’ve used the expression “I’ll go to the mat” countless times discussing a figurative willingness to tackle a challenge or fight a battle that had to be faced (I say it often when talking to fellow Autism Parents). @fredsonpaixao would not let me avoid going to the literal mat for myself. My training partners and friends welcome me, support, and lift me up every single time I show up on those mats. I am less afraid of my future because I actually do go to the mats, get uncomfortable learning how to fight for and defend myself, and am learning to embrace and push through conflict rather than paste on a smile tell a joke and avoid the conflicts that life absolutely does throw at all of us. Just a small thing, but the girl in the pink shorts accidentally bought them in a size small (haven’t worn an S in 20 yrs) and they fit🎉🎉🎉 not because I obsessed about my weight but because I fell in love with going to the mat for myself in BJJ and began applying the lessons learned there to other aspects of my life. Thank you @fredsonpaixaoacademylv for seeing something in me that I was hiding from myself and giving me the space and tools to start climbing out of my cocoon. 🙏🏻 #bjj #bjjtraining #bjjlifestyle #bjjgirls #girlswhoroll #livingmybestlife #babysteps #onedayatatime #justshowup #shefit #fabletics #underarmour #brazillianjiujitsu #weightlosstransformation #weightloss

I’ve worn @uahunt gear for awhile now, they’re synthetics are hard to beat in the Florida heat! 

I wear a mix of a few systems and patterns they offer. 

•Ridge Reaper Forest - for my spring Turkey hunts, and if I know I’m going to be in a more palmetto and pines area… or just about anywhere because the white in the pattern realy goes with the flashes of white all over the oaks, cypress trees and natural colors you may find in Florida swamps and bottomland.

Swipe to see the difference in the other pattern… 

•Ridge Reaper Barren - definitely my favorite all around and probably have worn the most, just because it has a bit of everything, you can clearly see in the second picture where a camo like this would shine, the dry months we have can bring serious grass and most of it becomes a very tan/brown color. Especially because one of my favorite local spots is always like that.. maybe I wear it more, I don’t know, but they are amazing in quality and I think very underrated !

Synthetics are a must in Florida, I can’t do merino.. wish I could but I would probably pass out on the way back in, just because I do try to hunt during the summer… which can be brutal. It’s all worth it after a nice spot and stalk hog!

❗️Straight Arm Cable Pulldown✖️
-
Although in the name .. Straight arm pull down, I like to bend slightly at the elbow at the bottom of the movement allowing more of a squeeze/contraction. 
-
I love this exercise & always have.. you really feel the LAT’s engaging in a long range of motion .. targeting the LATS mainly, other muscle come into play with this exercise;
•Lats
•Upper back
•Rear delts 
•Triceps
•Chest
•Core
-
An important tip to take with this exercise is to remember that as you reach the top of the movement (arms out stretched) to look down, then as you pull down, back straight & core engaged, look up. This really emphasises getting the most out of the movement & allows you to develop a steady but powerful flow .. engaging the core at all times allows you to build up your core stability also. 
-
Ideal for either a warm up, a main working set, or a cool down.. be sure to chuck this into your routine to mix things up if you haven’t already! ..

I DID IT!!!! 🥳🥳🥳

I have notched up 125km (roughly 78 miles) of running whilst fasting during this Holy month of Ramadan.

I've got a long way to go with regards to my marathon training. However, knowing that I was able to run whilst fasting will definitely help with the confidence moving forwards.

Besides the fasting, during Ramadan, Muslims will increase spiritual devotional acts such as prayer, reading the Qur'an, giving charity and strengthening family ties.

As you can imagine, it's been a very reflective period for me. I often question why I had my cardiac arrest. Doctors still haven't given me any clear reasons. Then one day through reading and praying I was hit with an epiphany:

when a person breaks a bone, the doctor may have to break the bone again to set it. Could it be that my heart was already broken and needed breaking again to create the conditions for healing?

I certainly do not take life for granted now and I've made amends with anyone I needed to. I've made big changes in my career, my location etc. just to make more time for my family as ultimately, that's what's precious to me. 

The pandemic has been tough, for everyone. However, during these long separations, distancing and missing people, have we all not realised just how much we love everyone?

I've not seen my Mum for over a year now. I miss her deeply. But when I call her and we both speak excitedly about being close to getting our second vaccines and hence closer to seeing each other again...I guess it's comparable to the Christmas countdown: it's awfully exciting!

Swipe through because it's these small points that can make a HUGE difference to your back development. A lot of it comes to what you do with your shoulder blades. As well as where you actually position your hands. Are you lining up it optimally with the lats fires? Or are you just pulling the weight around? A big with lat pulldowns is we want to relax the scapula(shoulder blades). All too often, people do one of two things. They ELEVATE their shoulder blades and hunch up during this movement. THIS is a big reason your shoulders and traps are on fire during this exercise. BUT then people try to counter this by depressing their shoulder blades. This isn't what you want either! Shoulders and traps are important stabilizers for the lat pulldown movement and we don't want to take them out of their Job. They are there for a reason in the movement. This will limit the range of motion and can cause joint instability (injuries). The key is to allow your shoulders to relax, focus on the movement when pulling towards you, think elbows anchor to the side. All of sudden you will notice, a much more fluid movement without any instability and comfort on the shoulders.
